features.name: PhdYeFM_antitox Antitoxin component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module
PIN Toxic component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module. An RNase

NAD_binding_1 Is involved in NO detoxification in an aerobic process, termed nitric oxide dioxygenase (NOD) reaction that utilizes O(2) and NAD(P)H to convert NO to nitrate, which protects the bacterium from various noxious nitrogen compounds. Therefore, plays a central role in the inducible response to nitrosative stress
